_attributes.Name: ASTDT
_attributes.Comment: AE.AESTDTC, converted to a numeric SAS date. Some events with partial dates are imputed in a conservative manner. If the day component is missing, a value of '01' is used. If both the month and day are missing no imputation is performed as these dates clearly indicate a start prior to the beginning of treatment. There are no events with completely missing start dates.

_attributes.Name: ASTDTF
_attributes.Comment: ASTDTF='D' if the day value within the character date is imputed. Note that only day values needed to be imputed for this study.

_attributes.Name: ASTDY
_attributes.Comment: IF ASTDT>=TRTSDT>MISSING then ASTDY=ASTDT-TRTSDT+1 Else if TRTSDT>ASTDT>MISSING then ASTDY=ASTDT-TRTSDT

_attributes.Name: AENDT
_attributes.Comment: AE.AEENDTC, converted to a numeric SAS date

_attributes.Name: AENDY
_attributes.Comment: IF AENDT>=TRTSDT>MISSING then AENDY=AENDT-TRTSDT+1 Else if TRTSDT>AENDT>MISSING then AENDY=AENDT-TRTSDT

_attributes.Name: ADURU
_attributes.Comment: If ADURN is not missing then ADURU='DAY'

_attributes.Name: AETERM
_attributes.{http://www.cdisc.org/ns/def/v1.0}Label: Reported Term for the Adverse Event

_attributes.Name: TRTEMFL
_attributes.Comment: If ASTDT >= TRTSDT > . then TRTEMFL='Y'. Otherwise TRTEMFL='N'

_attributes.Name: AOCCFL
_attributes.Comment: Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCCFL=Y) within each Subject

_attributes.Name: AOCCSFL
_attributes.Comment: Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), System Organ Class (AEBODSYS), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCCSFL=Y) within each Subject and SOC

_attributes.Name: AOCCPFL
_attributes.Comment: Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), System Organ Class (AEBODSYS), Preferred Term (AEDECOD), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCCPFL=Y) within each Subject, SOC, and PT

_attributes.Name: AOCC02FL
_attributes.Comment: Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and AESER='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCC02FL=Y) within each Subject

_attributes.Name: AOCC03FL
_attributes.Comment: Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and AESER='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), System Organ Class (AEBODSYS), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCC03FL=Y) within each Subject and SOC

_attributes.Name: AOCC04FL
_attributes.Comment: Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and AESER='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), System Organ Class (AEBODSYS), Preferred Term (AEDECOD), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCC04FL=Y) within each Subject, SOC, and PT

_attributes.Name: CQ01NAM
_attributes.Comment: If AEDECOD contains any of the character strings of ('APPLICATION', 'DERMATITIS', 'ERYTHEMA', 'BLISTER') OR if AEBODSYS='SKIN AND SUBC UTANEOUS TISSUE DISORDERS' but AEDECOD is not in ('COLD SWEAT', 'HYPERHIDROSIS', 'ALOPECIA') then CQ01NAM='DERMATOLOGIC EVENTS' Otherwise CQ01NAM=NULL

_attributes.Name: AOCC01FL
_attributes.Comment: Subset to CQ01NAM='' and TRTEMFL='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCC01FL=Y) within each Subject (Flag First Treatment Emergent Dermatological Event for Time to Event Analysis)

_attributes.Comment: The date of final dose (from the CRF) is EX.EXENDTC on the subject's last EX record. If the date of final dose is missing for the subject and the subject discontinued after visit 3, use the date of discontinuation as the date of last dose. Convert the date to a SAS date.
_attributes.{http://www.cdisc.org/ns/def/v1.0}Label: Date of Last Exposure to Treatment

_attributes.Name: CUMDOSE
_attributes.Comment: For ARMN=0 or 1: CUMDOSE=TRT01PN*TRTDUR. --- For ARMN=2: CUMDOSE will be based on 54mg per day for the # of days subj was in 1st dosing interval (i.e., visit4date-TRTSTDT+1 if 1st interval completed, TRTEDT-TRTSTDT+1 if subj discontinued <=visit 4 and > visit 3), 81mg per day for the # of days subj was in 2nd dosing interval (i.e., visit12date-visit4date if 2nd interval completed, TRTEDT-visit4date if subj discontinued <= visit 12 and > visit 4), and 54mg per day for the # of days subj was in 3rd dosing interval (i.e., TRTEDT - visit12date if subj continued after visit 12).

_attributes.Name: AGEGR1N
_attributes.Comment: AGEGR1 = 1 if AGE <65. AGEGR1 = 2 if AGE 65-80. AGEGR1 = 3 if AGE >80.
